 <mi>i</mi>
</msub>
</math>
 can lie inside the boundary. This is because, from <a href="#eq__2_2_1_1">(6)</a> <math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'>
<mrow>
 <msub>
  <mi>&#x3B2;</mi>
  <mi>i</mi>
 </msub>
 <mo stretchy='false'>=</mo>
 <mn>0</mn>
</mrow>
</math>
. Hence 
<ul class='lyxitem lyxitemii'>
<li class="itemize_item" id='magicparlabel-46'>from <a href="#eq__8_1_1sarfgqfg">(10)</a> it may be <math xmlns='http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML'>
